# Lumina Model Patterns

## Required Traits

Every Lumina model must use the following traits:

```php
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Factories\HasFactory;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\SoftDeletes;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HasValidation;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HidableColumns;

class Post extends \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    use SoftDeletes;
    use HasValidation;
    use HidableColumns;
}
```

## Static Properties for Query Control

Define which fields are available for filtering, sorting, searching, inclusion, and field selection:

```php
// Allowed filters for ?filter[field]=value
protected static $allowedFilters = ['status', 'category_id', 'created_at'];

// Allowed sorts for ?sort=field or ?sort=-field (descending)
protected static $allowedSorts = ['title', 'created_at', 'updated_at'];

// Default sort when none specified
protected static $defaultSort = '-created_at';

// Allowed sparse fieldsets for ?fields[model]=field1,field2
protected static $allowedFields = ['id', 'title', 'body', 'status', 'created_at'];

// Allowed includes for ?include=relation1,relation2
protected static $allowedIncludes = ['author', 'comments', 'tags'];

// Allowed search fields for ?search=term
protected static $allowedSearch = ['title', 'body'];
```

## Fillable Fields

Always define `$fillable` explicitly:

```php
protected $fillable = [
    'title',
    'body',
    'status',
    'category_id',
    'author_id',
];
```

## Validation Arrays

Define validation rules on the model itself:

```php
// Base validation rules applied to both store and update
protected $validationRules = [
    'title' => 'required|string|max:255',
    'body' => 'required|string',
    'status' => 'required|in:draft,published,archived',
    'category_id' => 'required|exists:categories,id',
];

// Fields required on store (simple format: field names only)
protected $validationRulesStore = [
    'title',
    'body',
    'category_id',
];

// Fields required on update (simple format: field names only)
protected $validationRulesUpdate = [
    'title',
];

// Custom validation messages
protected $validationRulesMessages = [
    'title.required' => 'Every post needs a title.',
    'status.in' => 'Status must be draft, published, or archived.',
];
```

## Pagination

```php
// Enable/disable pagination (default: true)
protected $paginationEnabled = true;

// Records per page (default: 15)
protected $perPage = 25;
```

## Ownership (Indirect Multi-Tenancy)

Lumina auto-detects the ownership chain by introspecting BelongsTo relationships. Just define the `belongsTo` relationship and Lumina will walk the chain to find the organization.

## Middleware

Assign middleware directly on the model, not in controllers:

```php
// Apply middleware to all actions
protected $middleware = ['verified'];

// Apply middleware to specific actions only
protected $middlewareActions = [
    'store' => ['throttle:10,1'],
    'update' => ['throttle:10,1'],
    'destroy' => ['can:admin'],
];

// Exclude specific CRUD actions (useful for custom route overrides)
protected $exceptActions = ['destroy'];
```

## Multi-Tenant Ownership

For models with a direct `organization_id` column, use the `BelongsToOrganization` trait:

```php
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\BelongsToOrganization;

class Project extends \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    use SoftDeletes;
    use HasValidation;
    use HidableColumns;
    use BelongsToOrganization;

    protected $fillable = ['name', 'organization_id'];
}
```

For models that belong to an organization indirectly (through another model), Lumina auto-detects the path from BelongsTo relationships:

```php
class Task extends \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    use SoftDeletes;
    use HasValidation;
    use HidableColumns;

    // Task -> Project -> Organization is auto-detected via BelongsTo
    protected $fillable = ['title', 'project_id'];

    public function project()
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(Project::class);
    }
}
```

## Complete Model Example

```php
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Factories\HasFactory;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\SoftDeletes;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HasValidation;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HidableColumns;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\BelongsToOrganization;

class Article extends \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    use SoftDeletes;
    use HasValidation;
    use HidableColumns;
    use BelongsToOrganization;

    protected $fillable = [
        'title',
        'slug',
        'body',
        'status',
        'author_id',
        'organization_id',
    ];

    protected static $allowedFilters = ['status', 'author_id'];
    protected static $allowedSorts = ['title', 'created_at'];
    protected static $defaultSort = '-created_at';
    protected static $allowedFields = ['id', 'title', 'slug', 'body', 'status', 'created_at'];
    protected static $allowedIncludes = ['author', 'comments'];
    protected static $allowedSearch = ['title', 'body'];

    protected $validationRules = [
        'title' => 'required|string|max:255',
        'slug' => 'required|string|max:255|unique:articles,slug',
        'body' => 'required|string',
        'status' => 'required|in:draft,published',
    ];

    protected $validationRulesStore = ['title', 'slug', 'body'];
    protected $validationRulesUpdate = ['title'];

    protected $paginationEnabled = true;
    protected $perPage = 20;

    protected $middleware = [];
    protected $middlewareActions = [
        'store' => ['throttle:10,1'],
    ];
    protected $exceptActions = [];

    public function author()
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(User::class, 'author_id');
    }

    public function comments()
    {
        return $this->hasMany(Comment::class);
    }
}
```

## DON'Ts

- **DO NOT** put authorization or authentication logic inside the model. Use Policies for authorization and Scopes for data filtering.
- **DO NOT** define inline query scopes for authorization purposes. Use dedicated Scope classes registered in the model's `booted()` method.
- **DO NOT** skip defining `$validationRules`. Every model exposed via the API must have validation rules to prevent invalid data.
- **DO NOT** use `$guarded` instead of `$fillable`. Always explicitly list fillable fields.
